In rural communities across America, the rate of suicide is twice as high in comparison to urban areas due largely to inaccessibility to mental health services and the stigma surrounding mental health.

As one of the leading causes of death in this country, suicide impacts individuals and families from all backgrounds. Suicide Prevention Month is about raising awareness regarding the risk factors and warning signs, as well as spreading hope. You are not alone.

If you or someone you know is struggling with suicidal thoughts, call or text the Suicide and Crisis Lifeline 988 or visit 988lifeline.org.
